---
title: Soy-Glazed Steak with Zucchini Stir-Fry plus Jasmine Rice & Scallion-Ginger Oil
description: This stir-fry is a flavor supernova! The star? Steak that you’ll sear, slice, and drizzle with a glossy soy glaze amped up with sweet chili sauce and nutty sesame dressing. Sprinkle that steak with crackly sesame seeds and serve it alongside a stir-fry of zucchini, scallion, and onion. Fluffy jasmine rice elevated with aromatic scallion-ginger oil rounds out this explosion of deliciousness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65950b71050f2b642e9a27af-ebb2afed.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65950b71050f2b642e9a27af.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/soy-glazed-steak-with-zucchini-stir-fry-65950b71050f2b642e9a27af
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 920 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 100 g
  sugar: 31 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1600 mg
cuisine: East Asia
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine ginger, scallion greens, 2 TBSP oil, and a pinch of salt. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir and set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, onion, and zucchini. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and ¼ cup water; cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, rice, and zucchini stir-fry between plates in separate sections. Drizzle any remaining sauce from pan over steak. Spoon as much scallion-ginger oil over rice as you like.

Garnish with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.